Student Resources

Centura College

Connecting Communities & Careers

Centura, offers training at 5 locations in Virginia and each campus is dedicated to helping students gain the skills and attitudes necessary to succeed. Drawing from over 30 years of career school experience, we are committed to the education and personal enrichment of each student.

See What Resources We Offer You

Get the Training

Centura College’s hands-on career training programs give you the skills you need to succeed in any industry.

Health Science
Looking for a career in health care? Get the training to work in the health care industry or as a medical practitioner.
Skilled Trades
Like working with your hands? Get the training you need to work in trades like Welding, HVAC, or Building Maintenance and Repair.
Business
You could become a business professional with our Business Management Degree Program. See more here.
Further Your Associate Degree
Graduates of an Associate Degree can increase their business skills while earning a Baccalaureate degree in Business. Learn more.
View All Of Our Programs

Student Services

At Centura, we put you first. Find out how we can help you achieve your educational goals.

General Students
Learn about the general student services offered to our students.
Military Students
Learn about the resources we offer to the men and women who were enlisted.
International Students
Learn about the resources we offer to international students.
Career Training Readiness Quiz

Campus Locations

Centura College‘s campuses are located throughout Virginia:

Chesapeake
Follow your dreams at our Chesapeake campus location.
Newport News
Expand your career possibilities at our Newport News campus location.
Virginia Beach
Learn a new skill at our Virginia Beach campus location.
Richmond
Learn a skilled trade at our Richmond Metro Campus Location.
Norfolk
View our available programs at our Norfolk campus location.
View All Of Our Campus Locations

Career Training
Our Locations
Student Resources

Centura College

Connecting Communities & Careers

Centura, offers training at 5 locations in Virginia and each campus is dedicated to helping students gain the skills and attitudes necessary to succeed. Drawing from over 30 years of career school experience, we are committed to the education and personal enrichment of each student.

See What Resources We Offer You

Get the Training

Centura College’s hands-on career training programs give you the skills you need to succeed in any industry.

Health Science
Looking for a career in health care? Get the training to work in the health care industry or as a medical practitioner.
Skilled Trades
Like working with your hands? Get the training you need to work in trades like Welding, HVAC, or Building Maintenance and Repair.
Business
You could become a business professional with our Business Management Degree Program. See more here.
Further Your Associate Degree
Graduates of an Associate Degree can increase their business skills while earning a Baccalaureate degree in Business. Learn more.
View All Of Our Programs

Student Services

At Centura, we put you first. Find out how we can help you achieve your educational goals.

General Students
Learn about the general student services offered to our students.
Military Students
Learn about the resources we offer to the men and women who were enlisted.
International Students
Learn about the resources we offer to international students.

Campus Locations

Centura College‘s campuses are located throughout Virginia:

Chesapeake
Follow your dreams at our Chesapeake campus location.
Newport News
Expand your career possibilities at our Newport News campus location.
Virginia Beach
Learn a new skill at our Virginia Beach campus location.
Richmond
Learn a skilled trade at our Richmond Metro Campus Location.
Norfolk
View our available programs at our Norfolk campus location.
View All Of Our Campus Locations

Career Training
Our Locations
Student Resources

Centura College

Connecting Communities & Careers

Centura, offers training at 5 locations in Virginia and each campus is dedicated to helping students gain the skills and attitudes necessary to succeed. Drawing from over 30 years of career school experience, we are committed to the education and personal enrichment of each student.

See What Resources We Offer You

Get the Training

Centura College’s hands-on career training programs give you the skills you need to succeed in any industry.

Health Science
Looking for a career in health care? Get the training to work in the health care industry or as a medical practitioner.
Skilled Trades
Like working with your hands? Get the training you need to work in trades like Welding, HVAC, or Building Maintenance and Repair.
Business
You could become a business professional with our Business Management Degree Program. See more here.
Further Your Associate Degree
Graduates of an Associate Degree can increase their business skills while earning a Baccalaureate degree in Business. Learn more.
View All Of Our Programs

Student Services

At Centura, we put you first. Find out how we can help you achieve your educational goals.

General Students
Learn about the general student services offered to our students.
Military Students
Learn about the resources we offer to the men and women who were enlisted.
International Students
Learn about the resources we offer to international students.
Career Training Readiness Quiz

Campus Locations

Centura College‘s campuses are located throughout Virginia:

Chesapeake
Follow your dreams at our Chesapeake campus location.
Newport News
Expand your career possibilities at our Newport News campus location.
Virginia Beach
Learn a new skill at our Virginia Beach campus location.
Richmond
Learn a skilled trade at our Richmond Metro Campus Location.
Norfolk
View our available programs at our Norfolk campus location.
View All Of Our Campus Locations

Career Training
Our Locations
Student Resources

Centura College

Connecting Communities & Careers

Centura, offers training at 5 locations in Virginia and each campus is dedicated to helping students gain the skills and attitudes necessary to succeed. Drawing from over 30 years of career school experience, we are committed to the education and personal enrichment of each student.

See What Resources We Offer You

Get the Training

Centura Colleges hands-on career training programs give you the skills you need to succeed in any industry.

Health Science
Looking for a career in health care? Get the training to work in the health care industry or as a medical practitioner.
Skilled Trades
Like working with your hands? Get the training you need to work in trades like Welding, HVAC, or Building Maintenance and Repair.
Business
You could become a business professional with our Business Management Degree Program. See more here.
Further Your Associate Degree
Graduates of an Associate Degree can increase their business skills while earning a Baccalaureate degree in Business. Learn more.
View All Of Our Programs

At Centura, we put you first. Find out how we can help you achieve your educational goals.

Learn about the general student services offered to our students.

Learn about the resources we offer to international students.

Norfolk
